## Gardening in Kashmir — local context

Kashmir's climate shapes what grows well and when outdoor work makes sense. Cold winters slow grass growth and can damage unpruned plants; spring and early summer are ideal for planting and lawn recovery; monsoon moisture encourages weeds if beds are neglected. Srinagar homes range from compact courtyard gardens to larger compounds that need regular attention.

When you book through Panun Kaergar, you are hiring professionals who understand local garden maintenance — not generic landscaping advice from far away. You can describe your space when booking — lawn size, number of beds, overgrown hedges, fallen leaves — and the assigned gardener arrives with appropriate tools for the visit.

For families who want a presentable outdoor space without spending weekends on upkeep, scheduled gardening visits keep things manageable year-round. Panun Kaergar's review system helps the community identify gardeners who consistently deliver quality work across Srinagar.

